UML:TaggedValue.value: We need to use special pattern for time dimension loading. The surrogate key must not be generated from database sequence, but we will use TO_NUMBER(TO_CHAR(D.DAY,'J')) expression.
Helper mapping for generating dates from 1.1.2006 to 1.1.2015.
Number of Product units involved in the Invoice.
Y for paid invoices. N for not paid invoices.
Time dimension. TIME_KEY is not generated from sequence, but is TIME_ID in julian format.

<u>Implicit dimension columns</u> [ALIAS]_KEY - Dimension surrogate key [ALIAS]_ID - Dimension natural key (ID in source system). [ALIAS]_VALID_FROM_DATETIME [ALIAS]_VALID_TO_DATETIME [ALIAS]_CURRENT_FLAG [ALIAS]_UPDATED_DATETIME All implicit dimension columns are not modeled except for natural key. Natural key is used in mapping, so it needs to be modelled.
<u>Implicit fact columns</u> [ALIAS]_UPDATED_DATETIME All implicit fact columns are not modeled.
<u>Fact column relations</u> For each BIRelation foreign key (named [ALIAS]_KEY) for target dimension is generated in fact table.
Id of customer in source system.
ALL_OBJECTS system view. This view contains many row and is used as mapping source when generating row is required.
